ass=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_24138801\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_24138801\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 27, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tfg1764053979457.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tfg1764053979457.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tfg1764053979457.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tfg1764053979457\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To use observability feature in Uniface, you need to configure the required settings as\n\t\texplained in the following sections.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tfg1764053979457__section_w396ab1b5b1_w397ab1b5_w398ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d801426e49\">Configuration Overview</h2>\n<div class=\"p\">By default, Observability is disabled. To enable it, add the following section to\n\t\t\t\tyour application's ASN\n\t\t\t\tfile:<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tfg1764053979457_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tfg1764053979457__codeblock_shs_thy_khc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[OBSERVABILITY]\nTRACE = on\nLOG = on\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"p\">Uniface uses the OTLP HTTP Exporter to send telemetry data to any backend that supports OTLP.\n\t\t\t\tConfigure endpoints in your ASN file as\n\t\t\t\t\tfollows:<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tfg1764053979457_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tfg1764053979457__codeblock_sqy_yhy_khc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">TRACE_ENDPOINT = http://yourhost:port/v1/traces\nLOG_ENDPOINT = http://yourhost:port/v1/logs\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div><div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"tfg1764053979457__note_owb_13y_khc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> TLS is not supported.</div></div>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Additional data to trace spans</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">The following setting to trace spans are disabled by default. You can switch them on\n\t\t\t\tto add additional telemetry data to trace spans.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tfg1764053979457_html_2\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tfg1764053979457__codeblock_j1j_w3y_khc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; Add $status as span attribute\nADD_PROC_STATUS = off\n; Add $proc_error as span attribute\nADD_PROC_ERROR = off\n; Add ProcScript profiling as span attributes\nADD_PROCPROFILING = off\n; Add ProcScript tracing as span events\nADD_PROCTRACING = off\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Span Processing Configuration</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\">These options control how trace spans are buffered and exported. All collected spans\n\t\t\t\tare first added to an internal queue, waiting to be processed. Once the queue\n\t\t\t\treaches its maximum capacity, any new spans will be dropped until space becomes\n\t\t\t\tavailable again. Spans in the queue are processed in batches, based on one of the\n\t\t\t\tfollowing conditions:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"tfg1764053979457__ul_bb3_2jy_khc\">\n<li class=\"li\">The number of queued spans reaches the defined batch size\n\t\t\t\t\t\t(<code class=\"ph codeph\">BATCH_SIZE</code>)</li>\n<li class=\"li\">The defined time interval (<code class=\"ph codeph\">SCHEDULE_DELAY</code>) has elapsed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">A configuration example:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tfg1764053979457_html_3\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tfg1764053979457__codeblock_cj4_gjy_khc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; Max number of spans in the buffer\nQUEUE_SIZE = 2048\n; Max spans exported in a batch\nBATCH_SIZE = 512\n; Time (ms) between exports\nSCHEDULE_DELAY = 5000\n; Max time (ms) to flush spans on shutdown\nFLUSH_TIMEOUT = 5000</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"p\">These values should be adjusted based on your system's environment—such as available\n\t\t\t\tmemory, network bandwidth, and the volume of telemetry data generated by your\n\t\t\t\tapplication.</p>\n<div class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Recommendation:</strong><ul class=\"ul\" id=\"tfg1764053979457__ul_awx_3jy_khc\">\n<li class=\"li\">Higher throughput applications should increase <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUEUE_SIZE</code>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tand <code class=\"ph codeph\">BATCH_SIZE</code> to reduce data loss and optimize\n\t\t\t\t\t\tperformance.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Latency-sensitive applications might prefer shorter\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">SCHEDULE_DELAY</code> for faster export.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Always balance performance with resource usage based on your deployment\n\t\t\t\t\t\tscenario.</li>\n</ul></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tfg1764053979457__section_gcv_phy_khc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d801426e138\">Configuration Reference</h2>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"igz1764054370664.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/igz1764054370664.html\" title=\"Use [OBSERVABILITY] section to control the behavior of the observability feature in Uniface. If the observability settings are not explicitly configured, the default settings are applied.\">[OBSERVABILITY]</a></p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_24138801\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_24138801\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Observability Setup Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 27, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 To use observability feature in Uniface, you need to configure the required settings as explained in the following sections. Configuration Overview By default, Observability is disabled. To enable it, add the following section to your application's ASN file: Explain this code [OBSERVABILITY] TRACE = on LOG = on Copy Uniface uses the OTLP HTTP Exporter to send telemetry data to any backend that supports OTLP. Configure endpoints in your ASN file as follows: Explain this code TRACE_ENDPOINT = http://yourhost:port/v1/traces LOG_ENDPOINT = http://yourhost:port/v1/logs Copy Note: TLS is not supported. Additional data to trace spans The following setting to trace spans are disabled by default. You can switch them on to add additional telemetry data to trace spans. Explain this code ; Add $status as span attribute ADD_PROC_STATUS = off ; Add $proc_error as span attribute ADD_PROC_ERROR = off ; Add ProcScript profiling as span attributes ADD_PROCPROFILING = off ; Add ProcScript tracing as span events ADD_PROCTRACING = off Copy Span Processing Configuration These options control how trace spans are buffered and exported. All collected spans are first added to an internal queue, waiting to be processed. Once the queue reaches its maximum capacity, any new spans will be dropped until space becomes available again. Spans in the queue are processed in batches, based on one of the following conditions: The number of queued spans reaches the defined batch size ( BATCH_SIZE ) The defined time interval ( SCHEDULE_DELAY ) has elapsed. A configuration example: Explain this code ; Max number of spans in the buffer QUEUE_SIZE = 2048 ; Max spans exported in a batch BATCH_SIZE = 512 ; Time (ms) between exports SCHEDULE_DELAY = 5000 ; Max time (ms) to flush spans on shutdown FLUSH_TIMEOUT = 5000 Copy These values should be adjusted based on your system's environment—such as available memory, network bandwidth, and the volume of telemetry data generated by your application. Recommendation: Higher throughput applications should increase QUEUE_SIZE and BATCH_SIZE to reduce data loss and optimize performance. Latency-sensitive applications might prefer shorter SCHEDULE_DELAY for faster export. Always balance performance with resource usage based on your deployment scenario. Configuration Reference [OBSERVABILITY] Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}